  "body": "Fixes #4617\r\n\r\nShort summary: we go down the following chain when we try to read data from containerd via grpc:\r\n\r\n1. [NewContentStore](https://github.com/containerd/containerd/blob/1ac546b3c4a3331a9997427052d1cb9888a2f3ef/content/proxy/content_store.go#L37) returns a `content.Store` implementation, specifically, [proxyContentStore](https://github.com/containerd/containerd/blob/1ac546b3c4a3331a9997427052d1cb9888a2f3ef/content/proxy/content_store.go#L31-L33)\r\n1. When attempting to get a reader via [proxyContentStore.ReaderAt](https://github.com/containerd/containerd/blob/1ac546b3c4a3331a9997427052d1cb9888a2f3ef/content/proxy/content_store.go#L93) returns a `content.ReaderAt` implementation, specifically [remoteReaderAt](https://github.com/containerd/containerd/blob/1ac546b3c4a3331a9997427052d1cb9888a2f3ef/content/proxy/content_reader.go#L26)\r\n1. When `remoteReaderAt` attempts to [ReadAt](https://github.com/containerd/containerd/blob/1ac546b3c4a3331a9997427052d1cb9888a2f3ef/content/proxy/content_reader.go#L37-L61), it calls `api/services/content/v1.ContentClient.Read()` [here](https://github.com/containerd/containerd/blob/1ac546b3c4a3331a9997427052d1cb9888a2f3ef/content/proxy/content_reader.go#L43) \r\n1. The protobuf-generated go code for [v1.ContentClient.Read()](https://github.com/containerd/containerd/blob/master/api/services/content/v1/content.pb.go#L1142-L1155) creates a [grpc.ClientConn.NewStream](https://godoc.org/google.golang.org/grpc#ClientConn.NewStream)\r\n\r\nThe comments on `NewStream` explicitly state:\r\n\r\n```\r\nctx is used for the lifetime of the stream\r\n```\r\n\r\nYet we have the single context for the entire life of the connection. With a short content blob, it doesn't matter; with a larger one, you have leakages of hundreds, thousands or tens of thousands of goroutines (and whatever other resources, like memory) are attendant to them.\r\n\r\nThis creates a derived child context for each `ReadAt()`, and therefore each `NewStream()`, and then cancels the child context _only_ as soon as the `ReadAt()` is done.\r\n\r\nSee the attached issue #4617 for much more detail. Short and simple test:\r\n\r\n1. Run `ctr content get` for some large blob\r\n1. While halfway through, do `kill -USR1 <ctr_pid>` or, if you don't mind killing it entirely, `kill -ABRT <ctr_pid>`\r\n1. See thousands of goroutines in `select` state with `grpc.newClientStream`\r\n1. Rebuild with this patch\r\n1. Repeat\r\n1. See exactly one goroutine in `select` state with `grpc.newClientStream` - it is fixed\r\n\r\nAs discussed with @dmcgowan ",
